trans-unit.source: The Media Service Management REST API may return the following error codes.
trans-unit.target: The Media Service Management REST API may return the following error codes.

trans-unit.source: For more information about status error codes, see <link xlink:href="10f8d244-4649-4063-b6c9-7a20765513fa" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Service Management Status and Error Codes</link>.
trans-unit.target: For more information about status error codes, see <link xlink:href="10f8d244-4649-4063-b6c9-7a20765513fa" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Service Management Status and Error Codes</link>.

trans-unit.source: 400 Bad Request
trans-unit.target: 400 Bad Request

trans-unit.source: Request contains wrong information and is rejected because of one of the following reasons:
trans-unit.target: Request contains wrong information and is rejected because of one of the following reasons:

trans-unit.source: The specified subscription ID is null or white-space.
trans-unit.target: The specified subscription ID is null or white-space.

trans-unit.source: The specified account name is not valid – A valid account name must be 3-24 lowercase alphanumeric chars.
trans-unit.target: The specified account name is not valid – A valid account name must be 3-24 lowercase alphanumeric chars.

trans-unit.source: Missing value for a required property (for example, account key).
trans-unit.target: Missing value for a required property (for example, account key).

trans-unit.source: Bad value for requested reserved units.
trans-unit.target: Bad value for requested reserved units.

trans-unit.source: 403 Forbidden
trans-unit.target: 403 Forbidden

trans-unit.source: Request cannot be allowed due to invalid certificate.
trans-unit.target: Request cannot be allowed due to invalid certificate.

trans-unit.source: 404 Not Found
trans-unit.target: 404 Not Found

trans-unit.source: Request tries to access a resource that does not exist.
trans-unit.target: Request tries to access a resource that does not exist.

trans-unit.source: Reason can be:
trans-unit.target: Reason can be:

trans-unit.source: The specified account name does not exist.
trans-unit.target: The specified account name does not exist.

trans-unit.source: The specified account storage account does not exist.
trans-unit.target: The specified account storage account does not exist.

trans-unit.source: The specified media service type does not exist.
trans-unit.target: The specified media service type does not exist.

trans-unit.source: 409 Conflict
trans-unit.target: 409 Conflict

trans-unit.source: An account with the specified account name already exists in this subscription.
trans-unit.target: An account with the specified account name already exists in this subscription.

trans-unit.source: Unable to create a DNS name for specified account.
trans-unit.target: Unable to create a DNS name for specified account.

trans-unit.source: 500 Internal Server Error
trans-unit.target: 500 Internal Server Error

trans-unit.source: The server encounters an error that stops request processing.
trans-unit.target: The server encounters an error that stops request processing.

trans-unit.source: The reason could be any unexpected error.
trans-unit.target: The reason could be any unexpected error.
